cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a novel imitation learning framework for learning branching policies for Mixed-Integer Linear Programming problems using Branch and Bound search. As such, it is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also introduces new input features and architectures to represent branching, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Finally, the use of parameterization to aid generalization suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
